text: many people don't believe me when I say
I've been to 133 countries as a 26 year
old all self-funded through teaching
English blogging social media and videos
so I'd like to dedicate this
three-minute video to introduce myself
and tell you how I got this far my name
is Drew Pinsky I'm that ginger travel
kid whose face may pop up on your
Facebook newsfeed because I make daily
travel videos so we drove up to the very
top of Swaziland for sunset I grew up in
sunny Scottsdale Arizona and I've been
obsessed with travel and geography ever
since my parents got me this globe for
my 10th birthday gift I traveled a lot
as a kid but only domestically I had
always dreamed of traveling the world
far and wide when college came around I
decided to attend the University of
wisconsin-madison I moved 2,000 miles
across country without knowing anybody
and I had the most incredible 4 years of
my life my first trip overseas was my
junior year when I studied abroad in
Prague that semester opened up my eyes
to the world where I visited about 20
countries it was at that point when I
knew I wanted to make a career out of
travel I went back to Wisconsin to
finish college graduated with a double
major in economics and entrepreneurship
and then immediately moved to South
Korea to teach English and avoid the
corporate world since it did not
interest me one bit I saw teaching as a
gateway to live and work abroad and it
was the best possible experience I could
have had at the time I started a travel
blog on day one in Korea and worked my
butt off for two years writing into my
fingers bled my goal with blogging was
to inspire young adults to travel and
step outside of their comfort zone which
is still my goal today but my blog is on
hold because I'm loving a video when I
left Korea I was starting to attract
sponsors for my blog which covered some
travel expenses so I started traveling
to India back to Europe to the Caribbean
to Southeast Asia to the Middle East
blogging transition into social media
mostly snapchat which transitioned into
making videos and then daily videos as
my following steadily increased over the
last 12 months my videos have had 87
point 2 million views as a result big
responders have come and now I'm making
a living from working with tourism
boards to promote
missions and travel brands to promote
experiences but these opportunities have
come as a result of very hard work and
patience I'm a workaholic whenever you
don't see me with a camera in my hand
you'll see me with a computer screen in
front of my face
always self-motivated and disciplined I
believe I have really found my niche
with short travel videos it's fun for me
it brings me happiness
it lets me be creative it lets me be
myself I cannot imagine doing anything
else
so what's next my eyes are set on
visiting every country in the world I
have 60 left and if all goes according
to plan I'll be done in mid 2020 which
is about 900 videos from now I can't
wait for the future and I just want to
say thanks again for joining me on this
wild ride i'm zhu ben ski and if you
like my travel videos please click
Subscribe and join me as i plan to visit
every country in the world
